	The Smith family is very grateful for all the support of friends, family, sponsors, and volunteers since our beginning in 2000. Together we are making a difference!\\n	While we continue to passionately work towards our cancer education and awareness mission, expanding our initiative to support early childhood development needs for children in our community is off to a great start. With the newest publication of The Color Rap Book and the distribution to kindergarten classes, we are helping young children begin their educational journey.\\n	Ann\'92s daughter Molly shared one of her special memories about her mother as a teacher: "My Mom always was able to relate to young children and they gravitated towards her... it was an amazing thing to watch. She spent many years of her teaching life with Kindergarten children. She would always say that they came into her classroom as babies at the beginning of the year, but by the end, they were little people learning to read and soaking up so much knowledge like little sponges!"\\n \\n	
