	The first edition of The Color Rap Book was presented as a Christmas gift in 2013 to Lauren Miller, a dear friend and teaching colleague of Ann, from her daughters, Amber and Ashley. Using materials similar to what Ann would have used in her classroom, they used tissue paper, construction paper and colored foils. Amber and Ashley compiled Ann\'92s raps and designed and printed the The Color Rap Book using a popular online photo service. In addition to presenting a copy to their mother, they also presented a copy to the Smith family. The Smith family was so impressed, they asked them to order more. In 2014, they found a print shop and ordered 500 copies. The copies were distributed to donors of the Ann Harris Smith Foundation and to a few local kindergarten teachers. The Smiths have been planning on the book\'92s second edition for several years. The first edition was well done however the foundation saw the potential to turn this gift \'96 originally intended to treasure on a personal level \'96 into one that could be given to incoming kindergarteners at local school districts for years to come.\\n	The second edition was printed in July 2019. The Smith family consider The Color Rap Book to be a wonderful opportunity to share Ann\'92s legacy, to inspire a new generation of teachers, and to continue to make learning fun. We believe she would be so happy and proud that so many people put in so much time and energy to put this all together and to care enough to try to get this into so many classrooms. The addition of this amazing app by our friend, Yuxin Liu, for the Ann Harris Smith Foundation has furthered our ability to reach families and support our mission of early childhood education.\\n \\n	
